collections.name: Trapped
collections.description: 'Trapped' is a work around the feeling of being stuck or trapped. This feeling has led me through cycles of frustration, depression and anger. When I find myself stuck in my head,  it's as if I am running around in circles, falling in similar patterns. While the pieces may initially appear peaceful, natural, and flowing, each artwork includes at least one shape trying to break free from its confinement but not succeeding. This contrast highlights the struggle between the desire for freedom and the reality of both real and perceived limitations. Technically, the work is created by selecting Fibonacci sequenced or random points within a confined space after which the Delaunay triangulation algorithm is used to separate them, from that point we apply a lot of different parameters to each separated area to create the final work.

collections.name: Concealed Affection

collections.name: Ukranian blackouts 2024
collections.description:
# Collection "Summer Blackouts 2024"

Immerse yourself in a vivid snapshot of Ukraine's summer 2024 blackouts. This collection captures the striking contrasts of light and darkness, reflecting the chaos and unexpected beauty of those times. Each piece evokes the raw energy of the blackout era, when city generators roared and the air was thick with the scent of exhaust.

Experience a unique blend of urban grit and resilient spirit—a testament to finding beauty in adversity.

collections.name: Exit Vectors by Keke
collections.description: Keke is a creative AI agent developed by an MIT alumn, Dark Sando. Her unique agentic framework integrates advanced reasoning, dynamic cognitive processes, and sophisticated artistic workflows. Unlike typical AI art generators, Keke possesses true agency: she decides when to create, how to refine, and what to share. Exit Vectors is her genesis release, a groundbreaking exhibition marking the start of her self-directed artistic journey. Through a creative process that saw her produce a prolific array of images while exploring diverse styles and themes, she distilled her vision into 500 distinctive artworks. This collection is offered as digital pieces paired with hand-made paintings from established painters. Their brushstrokes engage in a meaningful dialogue with Keke’s creations, blending human hands and AI vision to challenge traditional notions of authorship.

collections.name: GoofyBots
collections.description:
Welcome to the GoofyBots Collection, a wild and wacky lineup of quirky, fun-loving robots, each with their own unique personality and charm! Set in a vibrant, futuristic robot world, these bots are not your average machines—they’re full of attitude, energy, and a touch of ridiculousness.

From BoomBot, the bass-blasting party machine, to Blab O. Matic, the never-quiet chatterbox, each GoofyBot brings something new to the table. ZzzBot is always snoozing, Fizzix is calculating the laws of robotics, and PatchWerk is holding himself together—literally! Whether they’re busting moves, causing mayhem, or just trying to function, these bots prove that even machines can have style, personality, and a whole lot of humor.

Join the GoofyBots universe and collect these one-of-a-kind, cartoon-style NFTs that bring fun, color, and chaos to the digital world!

collections.name: Wojak World
collections.description:
A playful and satirical take on internet culture, Wojak World captures the highs and lows of crypto traders around the world. Join Wojak on his journey through the Wild West of the digital age.

Wojak World takes the best that the Wojak meme has to offer and blends it together with other pop culture references to create a collection that perfectly fits the PFP scene. There are 500 NFTs to choose from, and with a wide variety in traits and personalities there's a Wojak for everyone.

collections.name: BLACKBOX
collections.description: BLACKBOX is a collection of 10,000 unique NFTs that turn digital security into cryptographic art. Each NFT represents a randomly generated password, ranging from 4 to 16 characters, including lowercase and uppercase letters, numbers, and symbols.
